sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Nielsen Holdings PLC (Symbol: NLSN), where a total volume of 58,517 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 5.9 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 170.8% of NLSN's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.4 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $27 strike call option expiring May 17, 2019 , with 17,230 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.7 million underlying shares of NLSN.

Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 38,725 contracts, representing approximately 3.9 million underlying shares or approximately 73.9% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $165 strike call option expiring March 01, 2019 , with 2,495 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 249,500 underlying shares of CRM.

Especially high volume was seen for the $73 strike put option expiring March 08, 2019 , with 2,288 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 228,800 underlying shares of TGT.
